{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-15",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_15_hammett_128kb.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Every Crackpot",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 5,
  "page_total": 6,
  "page_start_sec": 986.48,
  "page_end_sec": 1227.08,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.639,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 986.48,
      "end": 987.84,
      "text": "Or number three,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 988.48,
      "end": 990.06,
      "text": "he sold Monaghan out to his",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 990.1,
      "end": 993.12,
      "text": "enemies and then fell out with them and they killed him."
    },
    {
      "start": 994.06,
      "end": 995.44,
      "text": "Or number four,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 995.66,
      "end": 996.6,
      "text": "Spade suggested"
    },
    {
      "start": 996.94,
      "end": 998.16,
      "text": "with a cheerful smile,"
    },
    {
      "start": 998.46,
      "end": 999.98,
      "text": "he died of old age."
    },
    {
      "start": 1000.2,
      "end": 1001.92,
      "text": "You folks aren't serious,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1002.1,
      "end": 1002.56,
      "text": "are you?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1003.03,
      "end": 1004.18,
      "text": "The two men stared"
    },
    {
      "start": 1004.42,
      "end": 1004.88,
      "text": "at Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1004.92,
      "end": 1006.02,
      "text": "but neither of them spoke."
    },
    {
      "start": 1006.976,
      "end": 1009.62,
      "text": "Spade turned his smile from one to the other of them and shook",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1009.62,
      "end": 1010.78,
      "text": "his head in mock pity."
    },
    {
      "start": 1011.76,
      "end": 1013.9,
      "text": "You've got Arnold Rothstein on the brain,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1014.14,
      "end": 1014.58,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 1015.584,
      "end": 1016.66,
      "text": "Brian smacked the back of",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1016.66,
      "end": 1018.96,
      "text": "his left hand down into the palm of his right."
    },
    {
      "start": 1019.64,
      "end": 1022.14,
      "text": "In one of those three categories lies the solution.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1023.14,
      "end": 1025.36,
      "text": "The power in his voice was no longer latent.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1026.34,
      "end": 1027.14,
      "text": "His right hand,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1027.24,
      "end": 1029.56,
      "text": "a fist except for protruding forefinger,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1029.84,
      "end": 1032.46,
      "text": "went up and then down to stop with a jerk"
    },
    {
      "start": 1032.84,
      "end": 1034.88,
      "text": "when the finger was leveled at Spade's chest."
    },
    {
      "start": 1035.68,
      "end": 1037.62,
      "text": "And you can give us the information that",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1037.62,
      "end": 1040.0,
      "text": "will enable us to determine the category."
    },
    {
      "start": 1041.248,
      "end": 1041.76,
      "text": "Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1041.98,
      "end": 1042.62,
      "text": "yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1042.92,
      "end": 1044.34,
      "text": "very lazily."
    },
    {
      "start": 1044.48,
      "end": 1046.02,
      "text": "His face was somber."
    },
    {
      "start": 1046.14,
      "end": 1048.3,
      "text": "He touched his lower lip with a finger,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1048.8,
      "end": 1049.68,
      "text": "looked at the finger,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1049.74,
      "end": 1051.76,
      "text": "and then scratched the back of his neck with it."
    },
    {
      "start": 1052.52,
      "end": 1054.96,
      "text": "Little irritable lines had appeared in his forehead.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1055.35,
      "end": 1057.48,
      "text": "He blew his breath out heavily through"
    },
    {
      "start": 1057.62,
      "end": 1060.46,
      "text": "his nose and his voice was an ill-humored growl."
    },
    {
      "start": 1061.28,
      "end": 1063.5,
      "text": "You wouldn't want the kind of information I could",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1063.5,
      "end": 1063.92,
      "text": "give you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1063.96,
      "end": 1064.22,
      "text": "Brian."
    },
    {
      "start": 1065.0,
      "end": 1065.96,
      "text": "You couldn't use it.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1066.88,
      "end": 1067.28,
      "text": "It'd poop",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1067.86,
      "end": 1069.9,
      "text": "this gambler's revenge scenario for you."
    },
    {
      "start": 1070.816,
      "end": 1072.72,
      "text": "Brian sat up straight and squared his shoulders.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1073.38,
      "end": 1075.24,
      "text": "His voice was stern without blustering.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1076.24,
      "end": 1077.66,
      "text": "You are not the judge of that.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1078.28,
      "end": 1078.84,
      "text": "Right or wrong,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1078.96,
      "end": 1080.78,
      "text": "I am nonetheless the district attorney."
    },
    {
      "start": 1081.792,
      "end": 1083.76,
      "text": "Spade's lifted lip showed his eye tooth.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1084.38,
      "end": 1086.01,
      "text": "I thought this was an informal talk."
    },
    {
      "start": 1087.08,
      "end": 1090.18,
      "text": "I am a sworn officer of the law 24 hours a day,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1090.44,
      "end": 1091.14,
      "text": "Brian said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1091.76,
      "end": 1093.1,
      "text": "and neither formality nor"
    },
    {
      "start": 1093.2,
      "end": 1097.38,
      "text": "informality justifies your withholding from me evidence of a crime,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1097.54,
      "end": 1098.08,
      "text": "except,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1098.22,
      "end": 1098.68,
      "text": "of course,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1098.92,
      "end": 1100.18,
      "text": "he nodded meaningly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1100.56,
      "end": 1102.66,
      "text": "on certain constitutional grounds."
    },
    {
      "start": 1103.19,
      "end": 1105.6,
      "text": "You mean if it might incriminate me?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1106.272,
      "end": 1106.9,
      "text": "Spade asked.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1107.04,
      "end": 1108.3,
      "text": "His voice was placid,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1108.3,
      "end": 1109.12,
      "text": "almost amused,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1109.12,
      "end": 1110.16,
      "text": "but his face was not."
    },
    {
      "start": 1110.68,
      "end": 1111.48,
      "text": "Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1111.58,
      "end": 1113.34,
      "text": "I've got better grounds than that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1113.74,
      "end": 1115.2,
      "text": "or grounds that suit me better."
    },
    {
      "start": 1115.82,
      "end": 1119.02,
      "text": "My clients are entitled to a decent amount of secrecy."
    },
    {
      "start": 1119.74,
      "end": 1123.98,
      "text": "Maybe I can be made to talk to a grand jury or even a coroner's jury,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1124.42,
      "end": 1126.78,
      "text": "but I haven't been called before either yet,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1127.34,
      "end": 1129.86,
      "text": "and it's a cinch I'm not going to advertise"
    },
    {
      "start": 1129.86,
      "end": 1132.94,
      "text": "my client's business until I have to."
    },
    {
      "start": 1133.88,
      "end": 1134.22,
      "text": "Then again,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1134.4,
      "end": 1136.58,
      "text": "you and the police have both accused me of"
    },
    {
      "start": 1136.58,
      "end": 1138.5,
      "text": "being mixed up in the other night's murders."
    },
    {
      "start": 1139.584,
      "end": 1141.24,
      "text": "I've had trouble with both of you before.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1141.74,
      "end": 1142.94,
      "text": "As far as I can see,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1143.0,
      "end": 1145.04,
      "text": "my best chance of clearing myself of"
    },
    {
      "start": 1145.04,
      "end": 1146.72,
      "text": "the trouble you're trying to make for me"
    },
    {
      "start": 1146.88,
      "end": 1149.9,
      "text": "is by bringing in the murderers all tied up."
    },
    {
      "start": 1150.8,
      "end": 1152.66,
      "text": "And my only chance of ever catching them",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1152.66,
      "end": 1155.34,
      "text": "and tying them up and bringing them in"
    },
    {
      "start": 1155.76,
      "end": 1158.12,
      "text": "is by keeping away from you and the police."
    },
    {
      "start": 1159.072,
      "end": 1160.9,
      "text": "Because neither of you show any signs",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1160.9,
      "end": 1163.6,
      "text": "of knowing what in hell it's all about."
    },
    {
      "start": 1164.7,
      "end": 1166.52,
      "text": "He rose and turned his head over his",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1166.52,
      "end": 1168.14,
      "text": "shoulder to address the stenographer."
    },
    {
      "start": 1169.248,
      "end": 1170.0,
      "text": "\"'Getting this all right,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1170.06,
      "end": 1170.26,
      "text": "son,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1170.9,
      "end": 1172.768,
      "text": "or am I going too fast for you?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1173.04,
      "end": 1176.16,
      "text": "The stenographer looked at him with startled eyes and replied,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1176.74,
      "end": 1177.02,
      "text": "\"'No,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1177.02,
      "end": 1177.2,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1177.34,
      "end": 1178.76,
      "text": "I'm getting it all right.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1179.616,
      "end": 1182.34,
      "text": "\"'Good work,' Spade said and turned to Brian again.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1183.02,
      "end": 1183.56,
      "text": "\"'Now,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1184.02,
      "end": 1187.78,
      "text": "if you want to go to the board and tell them I'm obstructing justice"
    },
    {
      "start": 1188.2,
      "end": 1190.32,
      "text": "\"'and ask them to revote my license,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1190.58,
      "end": 1191.46,
      "text": "hop to it."
    },
    {
      "start": 1192.28,
      "end": 1194.0,
      "text": "\"'You've tried it before and it didn't get",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1194.0,
      "end": 1196.28,
      "text": "you anything but a good laugh all around.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1196.64,
      "end": 1197.82,
      "text": "He picked up his hat."
    },
    {
      "start": 1198.84,
      "end": 1199.3,
      "text": "Brian began,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1199.58,
      "end": 1200.5,
      "text": "but look here,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1201.472,
      "end": 1202.02,
      "text": "Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1202.28,
      "end": 1205.72,
      "text": "and I don't want any more of these informal talks."
    },
    {
      "start": 1206.56,
      "end": 1208.78,
      "text": "I've got nothing to tell you or the police,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1208.96,
      "end": 1212.4,
      "text": "and I'm goddamn tired of being called things by every"
    },
    {
      "start": 1212.52,
      "end": 1214.22,
      "text": "crackpot on the city payroll."
    },
    {
      "start": 1215.1,
      "end": 1216.08,
      "text": "If you want to see me,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1216.24,
      "end": 1218.9,
      "text": "pinch me or subpoena me or something,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1219.34,
      "end": 1221.0,
      "text": "and I'll come down with my lawyer."
    },
    {
      "start": 1221.5,
      "end": 1222.98,
      "text": "He put his hat on his head,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1223.14,
      "end": 1223.24,
      "text": "said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1223.72,
      "end": 1225.47,
      "text": "see you at the inquest,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1225.6,
      "end": 1225.88,
      "text": "maybe,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1226.36,
      "end": 1227.08,
      "text": "and stalked out."
    }
  ]
}